## Retrospective

**Introduction**

Overall the team had a productive 2-week sprint to develop a strong base foundation including all the relevant aspects which will be needed for future development.

**Development**

This updates the existing codebase given to us by the clients who had previously overseen a project that worked on a similar solution. As this codebase was unfeasible to build on the team decided to scrap the code and rebuild it from scratch using NodeJS and React-Native.

**Communication**

The team made extensive use of communication channels on Discord to keep the rest of the team members up to date. This worked extremely well as all members gradually began using the team communication channels regularly which allowed everyone to be kept up to date and made organisation within the team very efficient and effective. We also conducted frequent face-to-face meetings with each other, the clients and project supervisor to keep the team heading in the right direction. In these meetings we spoke on tasks completed, tasks to complete and tasks that we needed clarification on which allowed us to stay on top of the work that we were required to complete by the end of the sprint.

**Methodology**

A suggestion for improvement would be to elicit more detailed deliverables for the following sprint from the clients. This sprint whilst asking for specific tasks although we were able to nail the main aspects some of the minor details which were important were left in the air which should be clarified so as to give the team a better understanding of what is within the scope of the project and what is out of the scope. This also allows the team to have a better understanding of where priorities should be and how time should be spent which allows for more effective time and task allocation to members.
